         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head><p>
               <supplied reason="lost">Presumably the emperor Nero</supplied> restored. <note>End of Latin text</note> 
                    By the action of Lucius Acilius Strabo, his personal deputy, he restored to the Roman People the boundaries 
                    <supplied reason="explanation">of the estates</supplied> which had been occupied by private persons.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>It is unlikely that the stone came from far away and it implies, therefore, the
                    presence of <foreign xml:lang="la">ager publicus</foreign> nearby.</p>
            <p>A boundary stone from a series defining the limits of estates belonging to the
                    Roman people, set up probably in the first year of Nero's reign, see
                    on <ref type="inscription">A08900</ref>. A Latin version of the Greek text given in
                    <ref type="inscription">A08900</ref>  preceded what survives here, either above or on
                    another face; most other stones in the series carried a full text of the Greek
                    version, as in <ref type="inscription">A08900</ref>, but here only the end is given.</p>
            <p>For Acilius Strabo see <bibl><ref type="external" 
               target="http://www.bbaw.de/forschung/pir/addenda/A/0082.html">PIR addenda</ref></bibl>; he was active in Cyrenaica under Claudius and 
               Nero: <ref type="inscription">A04000</ref>, <ref type="inscription">A08900</ref>, <ref type="inscription">A12210</ref>, 
               <ref type="inscription">C80400</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C80600</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C83700</ref>, 
               <ref type="inscription">C84000</ref> <ref type="inscription">C84100</ref>, 
               <ref type="inscription">C84300</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C84400</ref>, <ref type="inscription">C84500</ref></p>
         </div>
         
